## Black Fox
### Actively pursues the best predictive model for you

![](data:image/svg+xml;base64,)

Black Fox is strong and agile AI automation assistant capable for heavy-lifting required for neural network parameter optimization. Once in action the Black Fox relentlessly pursues the best posible predictive model for the data set at hand, and when caught the best model is readily delivered for further predictive analysis.

<iframe width="800" height="450" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/lFHAzup_sME?autoplay=1" frameborder="0" allow="accelerometer; autoplay; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture" allowfullscreen></iframe>

    


## Install Black Fox and dive right in

At present, Black Fox is available as a Python 3 package, while bindings for other languages are well underway. Black Fox is designed to be as unobtrusive as possible and fits in perfectly within any data science workflow. It can be installed from [PyPi](https://pypi.org/project/blackfox/) using a plethora of modern Python package managers, [pip](https://pip.pypa.io/en/stable/quickstart/), [pipenv](https://docs.pipenv.org/en/latest/) or [poetry](https://poetry.eustace.io). 

```console
 $ pip install -U blackfox
```

Dive in with your test and train data directly from an interactive Python session:

```python
 >> from blackfox import BlackFox
 >> bf = BlackFox()
 >> (nn_io, nn_info, nn_md) = bf.optimize_keras_sync(
      x_train, 
      y_train
   )
```

and you are good to go, the optimization will proceed for some time and finally you'll be granted the best posible predictive model. Take a look at our [documentation](./documentation/documentation.html) for details and our [examples](./examples/examples.html) in order to see how Black Fox can be used to solve some real-world problems.
